org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.job

Class JobResultImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.job.JobResultImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, JobResult

    public class JobResultImpl
extends Object
implements JobResult
    Class representing a job result. A job result is a map of task result. The key of the map is the name of the task on which to get the result. To identify the job result, it provides the id of the job in the scheduler and the job name.
    Since:
    ProActive Scheduling 0.9
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        public TaskResult getResult(String taskName)
                     throws UnknownTaskException
        Description copied from interface: JobResult
        Return the task Result corresponding to the given name. A result is returned if the taskName exist and if the result is available. Null is returned if the task is not finished (has no result).
